    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Awesome work @LukyVj it looks so good! 👏\r\n\r\nI have some remarks:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/27446912-5e28f5d2-577f-11e7-8a4c-0dc280e4cfa6.png) \r\nIt looks like the whole button should be clickable?\r\n\r\n ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/27447175-5ac41b1e-5780-11e7-917d-d64fa15e9e71.png) \r\nDid you tried with a white hover text color?\r\n\r\n\r\n![jun-22-2017 19-25-59](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/27447289-b4f15674-5780-11e7-85f2-b53f0a820956.gif) \r\nThe left side menu has a scrollbar inside itself and does not take the full height space of the page\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n* We lost the syntax color into code examples.\r\n* The get started CTA is only the third one, I expect from a documentation website to be almost the first thing visible to encourage users to start coding!\r\n* I think the get started link does not fit with the no framework needed block but more with the widgets one.\r\n\r\nAnd again thank's a it's so much better <3\r\nIf you need any help for anything just ask!",
