  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Indeed as a dev it was not obvious what this button does, it looks very similar to open link in a new window (something you generally don't want to happen): \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/123822/27535611-edfad61e-5a6b-11e7-8a4c-0bb8c6504cfa.png), from https://thenounproject.com/search/?q=popup%20window&i=539930\r\n\r\nWe could either have a nice text button with \"copy\" (no need for copy to clipboard) button, much like we have \"edit on github\". If we want to go for an icon, that one is more often seen in documentations: \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/123822/27535648-1347051e-5a6c-11e7-8518-e03bf1590691.png), from https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Octicons-clippy.svg. It's the copy button that was on GitHub for years and thus is something immediately recognisable by all developers.",
